  "extra": {
    "note": "EMBED -> RECOVER ROUNDTRIP. PART A (top): extract a palette, build a prompt, and the Metadata Embedder saves a PNG to ComfyUI/output with the prompt stored in a tEXt chunk. RUN PART A FIRST -- it writes ideogram_roundtrip_00001_.png. PART B (bottom): the Load Image With Prompt node opens that saved file BY PATH and recovers the embedded prompt, which the Validator then re-checks (point image_path at the file Part A wrote; adjust the counter if needed). The Metadata Reader at the bottom-left is wired to the loaded IMAGE tensor on purpose to demonstrate the caveat: a ComfyUI IMAGE tensor carries NO metadata, so it reports 'not found' -- which is exactly why Load Image With Prompt (file-based) exists. ShowText nodes are OPTIONAL (ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts); the embedder's own preview confirms the save without them. NOTE: tEXt metadata only survives in PNG -- re-saving as JPEG destroys it."
